The paper compares two fundamental theories in information theory and computer science, Shannon information and Kolmogorov complexity. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the basic notions of both theories, which involves coding, mutual information, sufficient statistics, and rate distortion theory. These topics are also relevant to the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
